OL,3,CMum who lost brother to suicide hopes
OL,4,Cto help others
OL,6,F"The girls I worked with were all
OL,7,Fknown to self-harm and many had
OL,8,Fattempted to take their own lives,"
OL,9,Fshe said. "They had it really tough at
OL,10,Fhome and needed help.
OL,12,F"I want to find answers to the
OL,13,Fquestions this work raised: what could
OL,14,Fschools do to support our young people
OL,15,Fand what support do schools need in
OL,16,Forder to do this."
OL,18,FFour out of five individuals
OL,19,Fconsidering suicide give some sign of
OL,20,Ftheir intentions, either verbally or
OL,21,Fbehaviourally.
